            <title>[KAFKA-17575] TestUtils.tempDirectory registers two shutdown hooks for the same thing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17575</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TestUtils.tempDirectory registers a shutdown hook to clean up the temporary directory on JVM exit. But it also calls file.deleteOnExit, which essentially does the same thing. There&apos;s no reason to do both, setting up a shutdown hook via Exit.addShutdownHook should be good enough.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
